Robert H. Mundheim 
University Professor of Law Emeritus






Education

LL.B.  - Harvard  - '57
B.A.  - Harvard  - '54




						Robert Mundheim began teaching at Penn in 1965.  Along with Noyes E. Leech, he established the Journal of International Economic Law in 1978. He has served as a General Counsel to the U.S. Department of Treasury and has been a special counsel to the S.E.C.  From 1982 to 1989, he served as the Dean of the Law School.  Under his Deanship, planning for the addition of Nicole Tanenbaum Hall began. 
					






