                    Publications
                

                    Events
                




English
Deutsch













        PLI’s Sixteenth Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe: Practical Implications of US Law on EU Practice
    

19-20 Jan 2017

                        
                            London
                        
                        

                        
                            Partner Rob Evans and of counsel Bob Mundheim (both New York-Capital Markets) spoke at PLI’s Sixteenth Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe: Practical Implications of US Law on EU Practice on January 19-20 in London. 





        Salzburg Global Forum on Corporate Governance
    

29 Sep – 1 Oct 2016

                        
                            Salzburg
                        
                        

Bob Mundheim, of counsel, and John Cannon, partner in Shearman & Sterling’s Compensation, Governance and ERISA Group and co-chair of the firm’s Corporate Governance Advisory Group, together with Simon Lorne, vice chair of Millennium Partners, L.P., facilitated a discussion among corporate directors and executives, investors, academics, lawyers, former regulators and corporate governance professionals from multiple jurisdictions on “The Corporate Balancing Act: How Can Directors Manage Conflicting Pressures?” at the Salzburg Global Forum on Corporate Governance held in Salzburg, Austria.





        Shearman & Sterling Lawyers Participate in Salzburg Global Seminar
    

1-3 Oct 2015

                        
                            Salzburg
                        
                        

John Cannon, chair of Shearman & Sterling’s Corporate Governance advisory group, Simon Lorne, vice chair of Millennium Partners, L.P., and Bob Mundheim, of counsel to Shearman & Sterling, co-chaired a three-day global seminar on “Corporate Governance in the Global Economy:  The Changing Role of Directors” on October 1-3 at the famed Schloss Leopoldskron in Salzburg, Austria, under the auspices of the Salzburg Global Seminar.  Georg Thoma, member of the Deutschebank Supervisory Board and of counsel to Shearman & Sterling, and Masahisa Ikeda, Managing Partner of the firm’s Tokyo office, also attended the seminar.





        Practical Law Institute's Thirteenth Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe
    

20-21 Mar 2014

                        
                            London
                        
                        

Barney Reynolds and Jo Rickard, partners, and Robert Mundheim, Of Counsel, spoke at Practical Law Institute's Thirteenth Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe on 20-21 March 2014 in London.
                        
                        




        Current Issues of Executive Compensation in the Financial Industry
    

9 Apr 2012

                        
                            Tuscon, Arizona
                        
                        

                        
                            Partner John Cannon (New York-Compensation, Governance & ERISA) and Of Counsel Bob Mundheim (New York-Capital Markets) spoke at a conference hosted by the James E. Rogers College of Law of The University of Arizona on April 9 in Tuscon Arizona, "Current Issues of Executive Compensation in the Financial Industry." Scholars from both finance and law fields tackled issues in executive compensation contributing to the collapse of financial institutions and in assessing subsequent regulation to prevent its recurrence.
                        
                        




        PLI's Tenth Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe
    

24-25 Jan 2011

                        
                            London
                        
                        

                        
                            Partners Richard Price and Jo Rickard and Of Counsel Bob Mundheim spoke at Practising Law Institute's 10th Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe: A Contrast in EU & U.S. Provisions on 24-25 January 2011 in London.
                        
                        




        Securities Regulation in Europe: A Contrast in EU & U.S. Provisions
    

25-26 Jan 2010

                        
                            London
                        
                        

                        
                            Partner Richard J.B. Price (London-Capital Markets) and Of Counsel Robert H. Mundheim (New York-Capital Markets) spoke at PLI’s Ninth Annual Institute on Securities Regulation in Europe on January 25-26, 2010.
                        
                        




        Forty-First Annual Institute on Securities Regulation
    

4 Nov 2009

                        
                            New York
                        
                        

                        
                            Of Counsel Robert Mundheim (New York-Capital Markets) will be speaking at the Practising Law Institute’s “Forty-First Annual Institute on Securities Regulation”.
                        
                        




        Global Capital Markets and the US Securities Laws 2009: Strategies for the Changing Regulatory Environment
    

20 May 2009

                        
                            New York
                        
                        

                        
