Insider Activity


Individual




Robert H. Mundheim



Mr. Robert H. Mundheim is Independent Director at Gogo, Inc., a Professor-Corporate Law & Finance at James E. Rogers College of Law, Of Counsel at Shearman & Sterling LLP, and Council Member at The American Law Institute. He is on the Board of Directors at Gogo, Inc., Gogo LLC, The New School, The Curtis Institute of Music, and Salzburg Global Seminar.
Mr. Mundheim was previously employed as Executive Vice President & General Counsel by Salomon, Inc., a Managing Director by Salomon Brothers Asset Management, Inc., Co-Chairman by Fried, Frank, Harris, Shriver & Jacobson LLP, Vice Chairman by Financial Industry Regulatory Authority, Inc., General Counsel by US Department of The Treasury, a Professor by University of Pennsylvania, Special Counsel by US Securities & Exchange Commission, Chairman by Quadra Realty Trust, Inc., Senior Executive Vice President & General Counsel by Citigroup Global Markets Holdings, Inc., and a Trustee by The American Academy in Berlin. He also served on the board at eCollege.com+ and Arnhold & S. Bleichroeder Holdings, Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from Harvard College, a graduate degree from Harvard Law School, and a graduate degree from the University of Pennsylvania.



