Robert H. Mundheim: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 10:29 AM ET
Professional Services

Company Overview of Shearman & Sterling LLP



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Robert H. Mundheim  Counsel, Shearman & Sterling LLPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships84--
Background

		Mr. Robert H. Mundheim has been Of Counsel to Shearman & Sterling LLP since 2000. Mr. Mundheim was Executive Vice President and General Counsel of Salomon, Inc. from 1992 to 1997. Mr. Mundheim was the Senior Executive Vice President and General Counsel of Salomon Smith Barney Holdings Inc. from 1997 to 1998. Since 2012, Mr. Mundheim has also served as a Professor of Corporate Law and Finance at the University of Arizona James E. Rogers College of Law. He was Co-Chairman ... of the New York law firm of Fried, Frank, Harris, Shriver & Jacobson LLP and University Professor of Law and Finance at the University of Pennsylvania Law School, where he taught since 1965. He was the University Professor of Law and Finance at the University of Pennsylvania from 1980 to 1992 and the Dean of the University of Pennsylvania Law School from 1982 to 1989. In addition, Mr. Mundheim has served as General Counsel of the U.S. Treasury Department from 1977 to 1980 and as Special Counsel of the Securities & Exchange Commission from 1962 to 1963. He served as Chairman of the Board of Quadra Realty Trust, Inc since February 2007. He serves as an independent Director of a number of publicly held companies (Union Capital Corporation, First Pennsylvania Bank, CoreStates Bank N.A., .). He has been an independent Director of Benjamin Moore & Co since 1997. He has been an Director at Gogo Inc since March 30, 2012. Mr. Mundheim is a Director at Arnhold, First Eagle Investment Management, LLC and S. Bleichroeder Advisers, LLC. He has been Director of CCH Incorporated (Commerce Clearing House, Inc) since 1981. He also serves as a Trustee and past President of the American Academy in Berlin; a Director and past President of the Appleseed Foundation; and Trustee of the New School University. He is a member of the Council of the American Law Institute and Chairman of its Governance Committee. Mr. Mundheim is also the Chairman of the Legal Advisory Boards of NASDAQ and the NASD. He served as member of the Supervisory Board of Hypo Real Estate Holdings AG from June 04, 2004 to January 31, 2007. He was independent Director of eCollege.com from January 2001 to 2007. He served as Vice Chairman, Governor-at-Large and a member of the Executive Committee of the National Association of Securities Dealers. He serves as a Trustee of the Curtis Institute of Music. He has served as a Consultant to the American Law Institute's Principles of Corporate Governance: Analysis and Recommendations from 1978 to 1994, as a member of the American Bar Association President’s Task Force on Corporate Responsibility from 2002 to 2003 and as a member of the Association of the Bar of the City of New York’s Presidential Task Force on Lawyers’ Role in Corporate Governance. He received BA from Harvard College and LLB from Harvard Law School.Read Full Background




